Virgo Key words - I Serve Your restrained, shy and somewhat serious exterior hides a soft and cheerful inner self which people appreciate once they get to know you. Often you are misunderstood on face value but worthy friends and associates see beyond the surface. Work and service are most important in your life and will be the prime outlet for your creative impulses. At times your desire to perfect every single details of a project, makes you prone to fastidiousness, overwork and dissipation of valuable resources on irrelevant aspects of work and friendship. Some people regard you as highly critical, though your motive stems from an innate ability to analyse, organise and systematically solve problems. Be aware that you must avoid the temptation to unconsciously nit-pick each and every person that comes you way or you may actually have the opposite effect than that desired. Your life will only find true meaning in the ideal of helping and serving others, leading a life of self sacrifice and simplicity. Health, hygiene and food or related industries should allow your nature to unfold to its optimum and contribute valuably to the world.

I had to go into hospital over the wkend. I went to the emergency department of Royal Adelaide Hospital on Sunday afternoon because I was feeling really sick! I had the WORST abdominal pains ever. I was at work and felt really sweaty, hot and had this really uncomfortable pains in my stomach. It went right across and through to my back. The nurses where I work said I looked really pale. I was only at work for about an hour or so and then got sent home. It just came on so fast.

I threw up THREE FUCKING TIMES! Gross I saw what I ate for lunch in there. I swear it has put me off eating hot chips ever again.

So I went to the hospital Sunday night and they gave me Morphine and some other drug. They also put up a drip. They had no idea what really was wrong with me. They thought it could have been my appendix or ovaries but they didn't really know. The doctors and the nurses were really nice. I was in so much fucking pain... it was unbelievable. My Mum said I was probably experiencing what labour is like lol... no I wasn't pregnant! Anyway I got sent home last night THANKGOD I didn't want to stay in hospital over night. They gave me some Panadeine Forte and so far everything has calmed down. I still get this weird feeling every now and then in my abdomen but it isn't at all bad. I was crying and everything. Very bad.

Just thought I'd let you know. The rest of my wkend was good. Lol.

Xoxo

I had a nice weekend. I worked Saturday and Sunday morning. I still managed to see Justin Saturday night. We went out for tea at Glenelg. We had chinese and then after we had cold rock! Yum I love that icecream. He had a really nice icecream peanut chocolate swirl or something. I had white chocolate icecream and M&Ms it was okay. Cookies and cream is heaps better though!

I have been writing my ethics essay for uni over the last week. I have finally finished. I will be happy passing. I really don't care. It is only 15%.

The holidays are coming up after Thursday. I'm working about 26 hours a week in the hols though. It will be good money coz I need the money bad..... coz I have to pay for all this stuff for my car very soon.

Justin wants me to go to Oakbank on Monday not sure if I will go! Lol. I've been before and it was pretty boring. He's going away this weekend with his mates up the river to Loxton. I hope they have fun. I know they will coz they will get pissed. I'm going out Saturday night with some of my friends to the city. That will be fun coz I haven't been out since the bus tour which is awhile ago now.

I'm staying at Justin's this Wednesday and Thursday. Thursday night his family and I are going to 'The Red Sea On Rundle'. For anyone who watches My Restaurant Rules will know what I'm talking about! If not then you will have no idea. But we're going there for tea for his Mum's bday. It should be interesting. I've heard its expensive there though :( I think its seafood :) So a plus and a minus lol.

I'm getting my hair cut and dyed on Thursday at Marion Hair and Beauty. I haven't been there before but my friend suggested it. So we will see how that goes!

I think that is about all my news for now. I start my clinical placement when the holidays end!!! Arghhhh! Lol.

Xoxoxoxoxoxxo

Anyway I'm going to go and have some tea.. I'm fucking starving!

Anyway, there isn't much more goss. I'll fill you guys in after the wkend. I prob won't update till at least Monday coz I'm staying at Justin's all wkend. Have a nice time everyone!

My first was in low care on Saturday which was easy. Today I worked as well and tomorrow I work!!! I'm learning... so that is good! The residents are quite funny at times. Actually on Saturday we had a big fucking walk as well coz no one could decide where they wanted to eat so we walked around half of adelaide, lol.

Anyway, I really can't wait for this wkend coz it's the BUS TOUR! I have been waiting for this wkend for ages haha. We are going to- Frostbites, Black Cat White Cat, Urban and the Church. It should be good. I've only ever been to the Church. I have heard the others are good. Hopefully they play heaps of rnb.

It is fun to wear that stuff though for a change. I do feel as though I'm important in my nursing uniform! Haha. Sorry Personal Carer Uniform! Lol.

I brought a top from Valleygirl which I might wear Saturday night. I think Bec and I are going shopping on Friday at Harbour Town and Glenelg. I'm looking for a cute denim skirt to wear out on Saturday night. I also saw this gorgeous pink and white playgirl bunny bag at Glenelg which I may have to purchase..... my money is pretty zilch at the moment though because I haven't been paid for a week since I quit at the supermarket and I won't get paid for another week! Arghhhhhh it's causing me stress!

I must leave now anyhow because Malcolm In The Middle is on. I just want to leave by saying Justin is a sweetie he sends me cute text messages!!!! Haha I'm heaps happy how stuff has worked out. I'm gonna go eat my white chocolate and watch Sex and The City later on if I can stay awake. Cya guys.

I want to take him home with me!

I had my exam today. I think I went okay. I think I passed. Argh I better have passed! It was mostly the same questions but worded diferently. Some of the really difficult questions were missing as well which was great! It was lucky I read up on all the stuff from the last exam!!

I went to the gym today as well and my fucking legs hurt!!! Lol see where exercise gets ya? ;)

I start my new job tomorrow. Well actually it is an orientation day! Fuck I'm still nervous though. It is such a relief that I have that stupid exam out of the way now though. Phewwwwwww, uni starts in 2 weeks!

Anyway, I'm going to watch 'The Simple Life'. Paris Hilton makes me laugh coz she is so dumb. Catch you guys soon.

Xoxo

These questions are from , thanks! 1. What field of nursing are you hoping to get into, and why did you choose it? I'm hoping to get into theatre. I think that area of nursing would be really interesting for me. I choose nursing as a career because I wanted to help people. I wanted to make a difference to someone's life. I wanted a job which I found rewarding. Also something which attracted me to nursing is probably the travelling which can be done with the career. I thought that was exciting. 2. Why did you start a journal on LJ? I started a journal because I thought it would be fun. It is a good place to vent or just generally to express your emotions and receive the opinions of other people. I generally like receiving comments from people and getting their feedback. 3. If you could only do one thing for the rest of your life, what would it be and why? It took me awhile to think about this one but.... I would shop. I love shopping. Buying clothes, shoes and bags. I love the markets. I love shopping malls. I love looking for bargains. It's just fun. I only hate food shopping! haha. 4. Where do you see yourself in 10 years? In 10 years I would be 29. Hopefully by then I will be successful in my chosen career- nursing. By that time I also hope that I have travelled many times overseas maybe even lived over there for sometime. I also hope to settle down, buy a house, a dog/cat (very important!!) and start a family. Oh, and of course I will have my celica by then! 5. Who's your favorite person in the world and why? That is a tough one! I don't know if I have one favourite person. There are alot of people who inspire me which I think is important. My family, friends, tutors from uni and people I work with. I think it depends what type of mood your in to answer this question! Lol. Everyone is probably important at some stage in your life. THE RULES: 1 - Leave a comment, saying you want to be interviewed. 2 - I will respond; I'll ask you five questions. 3 - You'll update your journal with my five questions, and your five answers. 4 - You'll include this explanation. 5 - You'll ask other people five questions when they want to be interviewed.
